# Ensure all entities are connected
# All Resources are connected to a ProductModel, a Locus, and managed by an Agent.
# All Resources are connected to at least one Application (Monitoring Platform).
# All NetworkInterfaces are connected to a Resource and a NetworkLink.
# All NetworkLinks connect at least two NetworkInterfaces (or one to external).
# All Applications have a managing Agent and type.
# All ApplicationModules are part of an Application and have status/SLA.
# All Services are composed of Applications/Modules.
# All EventRecords have originating object/system/agent and time/text.
# All TroubleTickets are triggered by an EventRecord, related to services/resources/parties, and have status/severity.
# All TroubleTicketNotes are part of a TroubleTicket.
# All ChangeRequests are related to resources/applications/parties and have status/cause.
# All OperationPlans have pre/post conditions.
# All DocumentAttachments are part of a TroubleTicket/ChangeRequest.

# This graph is designed to be dense and interconnected, reflecting a complex IT environment.
# The use of various NORIA properties ensures a rich description of each entity and its relationships.
